review_res.text: I compare a pair and arrange them, then use those "points" to compare and sort the rest. I think you can reduce the number of comparisons necessary by starting by comparing an unknown to something in the middle of the knowns. Then you know which side it is on and you don't have to make any comparisons with the other side.
